📄 1. Project Summary — What We Did

Project: RAG Chatbot UI with Free AI Integration
Tech Stack: Next.js 16.x, TypeScript, React 19.x, OpenRouter, Vercel deployment

🛠 Initial Setup

Created a RAG chatbot UI using Next.js + TypeScript

Installed AI SDK and UI components for streaming chat UI using @ai-sdk/react and related elements

🔑 API Key Integration

Originally used @ai-sdk/openai and OpenAI API key

Switched to OpenRouter to use free/inexpensive models for the demo

Stored credentials in .env.local:

OPENAI_API_KEY=...
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=...

Updated API route (src/app/api/chat/route.ts) to use:

import { createOpenRouter } from "@openrouter/ai-sdk-provider";
const openrouter = createOpenRouter({ apiKey: process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY! });

This ensures no reliance on paid OpenAI keys in production.

💡 UI Enhancements

Added a message banner above the chat input to note that this uses free AI with limitations, setting user expectations

Updated chat UI (/chat/page.tsx) to show streaming responses and a human‑friendly interface

⚠ Fixing Deployment Issues

Encountered dependency resolution/build errors on Vercel because of strict peer dependencies with React 19.x

Added a .npmrc file with:

legacy-peer-deps=true

to tell npm to ignore strict peer conflicts on deployment

Also set both OPENAI_API_KEY and OPENROUTER_API_KEY in Vercel’s environment, since some AI SDK code still checks for OpenAI env.

🔧 TypeScript Runtime Fixes

Build failed due to unmatched tool UI states (approval-requested, etc.)

Patched src/components/ai-elements/tool.tsx to include all possible tool states and corresponding icons/labels — this satisfies TypeScript and builds successfully.

🧹 Dependency Cleanup

Removed unused package @ai-sdk/openai

Performed clean reinstall with:

npm install --legacy-peer-deps

Ensured the project builds both in dev and production modes

🚀 Deployment

Verified deployment on Vercel

Ensured environment variables were set correctly

Triggered production build, validated no missing keys or TypeScript errors

🧠 Next Steps (Optional Improvements)

Implement local testing suite (unit tests/E2E tests)

Add automated type‑checking in CI

Add screenshot, live demo links to the README section
